<subSubSection pageId="238" pageNumber="239" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="238" pageNumber="239">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="238" pageNumber="239">This rare species, also known as the &quot;Alpine Tiger Beetle&quot;, ranges from southern Idaho to south-central Oregon, south to east-central California and west-central Utah [see Pearson et al. 2006: Map 31]. The record from one locality in northern Montana (see Pearson et al. 2006: Map 31) is possibly based on a stray.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
